/timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132516959.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[After being presumed extinct for sixty years, a remarkable coral reef off West Africa has been rediscovered, thriving with an array of fish and coral species. This vibrant mesophotic coral ecosystem thrives in low-light environments beneath the ocean's surface. Researchers speculate that similar hidden reefs could exist along the West African coastline, providing valuable insights into the evolutionary history of the region's marine life and past environmental changes.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-marked-this-west-african-coral-reef-as-probably-dead-in-the-1960s-underwater-drones-found-it-alive-more-than-50-metres-below-the-sea/articleshow/132516959.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-marked-this-west-african-coral-reef-as-probably-dead-in-the-1960s-underwater-drones-found-it-alive-more-than-50-metres-below-the-sea/articleshow/132516959.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T19:49:04+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132517609,imgsize-239610.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[FedEx CEO Raj Subramaniam grabbed the opportunity that his roommate rejected: He can't come but can I send my resume?]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132517128.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/fedex-ceo-raj-subramaniam-grabbed-the-opportunity-that-his-roommate-rejected-he-cant-come-but-can-i-send-my-resume/articleshow/132517128.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/fedex-ceo-raj-subramaniam-grabbed-the-opportunity-that-his-roommate-rejected-he-cant-come-but-can-i-send-my-resume/articl